Thailand May Raise Taxes on Alcohol, Cigarettes, Post Today Says

-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 
2011-09-16T01:06:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-16/thailand-may-raise-taxes-on-alcohol-cigarettes-post-today-says.html
Thailand  may raise excise taxes on
alcohol and cigarettes to fund government spending increases,
Post Today reported, citing an unidentified finance ministry
official.  The tax increase may provide an additional 20 billion baht
of revenue, the Thai-language newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anuchit Nguyen in Bangkok at 
 anguyen@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tony Jordan at 
 tjordan3@bloomberg.net  